Honda shares down on profit - taking . Shares in Honda Motor Co Ltd slipped on Thursday morning as profit - taking emerged after the recent sharp rally , traders said . The auto maker ' s share price was down 70 yen at 3 , 400 yen at 0051 GMT . Volume was 2 . 798 million shares , making it the second - heaviest volume on the first section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange . " The pace of the rally was too quick , so profit - taking emerged . Technically speaking , the price had deviated 18 percent from the five - week moving average and trade had been overheated , " said a broker at a major securities house . 
